permalink: /Symbolist Nature Poetry (19th–20th century)/Yves Bonnefoy/Yves Bonnefoy - Tapestry of Existence
---

Life in its myriad forms
Blooms in the whispers of the wild,
Where every creature plays a part,
In this grand tapestry of existence,
With the wind as their muse,
They dance in perfect harmony,
And in the symphony of nature,
We find ourselves entwined,  
The beauty of being alive.

- Yves Bonnefoy
